You are calling `repeat` twice, so therefore it is printing twice.
```C
repeat();
c = repeat();
```

Try replacing the first call to repeat to `getchar()`. This will consume the character entered after the modifer line.
```C
getchar();
c = repeat();
```

It looks like you are just starting to learn C, and it might be worthwhile to read a book on the matter. One that I can recommend is [Modern C][1]. It&#39;s available free online, or you can buy a print version.


  [1]: https://modernc.gforge.inria.fr/

