There is an instance property called `preferredScreenEdgesDeferringSystemGestures` which can be overridden. This will not disable the notification center, but it will force the user to swipe twice – the first time, a small tab will extend from the top of the screen instead.  Add the following code to your view controller:

    override var preferredScreenEdgesDeferringSystemGestures: UIRectEdge {
        return .top  //Or, return .all to &quot;disable&quot; the control center as well
    }

